"Also serves as: 'ten sample tile levels' via the ASCII format from
Chapter 8. Two things a book of arcade games can't ship without.

## Part 1 — The cabinet skeleton

Every arcade game has the same outer loop. Chapter 14 built it.
Here is the skeleton stripped of game-specific parts. Copy this
into any new game.

```scheme
(define game-state 'attract)
(define state-timer 0)

(define (transition new-state)
  (set! game-state new-state)
  (set! state-timer 0)
  (case new-state
    ((play) (init-play))))

(define (init-play)
  (world/reset!)
  ;; your game setup here
  )

(define (game-frame)
  (set! state-timer (+ state-timer 1))
  (paint-clear)
  (case game-state
    ((attract)
     (paint-attract)
     (when (input/pressed? 'a) (transition 'play)))
    ((play)
     (game-play-tick)
     (when (game-over?) (transition 'game-over)))
    ((game-over)
     (paint-game-over)
     (when (> state-timer 180) (transition 'attract)))))

(define (arcade-cabinet) (transition 'attract) (on-frame game-frame))
(big-bang arcade-cabinet)
```

Fill in `paint-attract`, `paint-game-over`, `init-play`,
`game-play-tick`, `game-over?` — you have a full cabinet. Every
game in this book fits this template.

## Part 2 — Ten sample tile levels

Chapter 8's parser maps `#` to solid tile, `.` to air, `P` to
player-spawn, `G` to goal. Here are ten levels you can run today
by dropping them into `parse-level` from chapter 8.

### Level 1 — Straight run

```
'(\"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"P......................G\"
  \"########################\")
```

Walk. Introduce nothing.

### Level 2 — First gap

```
'(\"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"........................\"
  \"P.......................G\"
  \"##########....##########\")
```

Jump a gap. First pressure.

### Level 3 — Rising steps

```
'(\"........................\"
